    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Headgear comprising circular or U-shaped garlands made from the leaves and branches of the laurel tree. An example is as worn by Roman commanders during the triumphal procession after a martial victory.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
